Write a title validation function which takes a string as an argument
and validates it by the rules:
- title can contain letters and special characters: [!,:,-,?,.,,].
- title length must be more than 2 characters but less than 20;
- title must start with an uppercase letter;

Function should return ‘VALID’ if the string meets the requirements or
‘INVALID’ if it does not.
Do not use regular expressions.
validateTitle(‘Title!’) -&gt; ‘VALID’
validateTitle(‘s’) -&gt; ‘INVALID’
validateTitle(‘12title’) -&gt; ‘INVALID’